# Site Page Standards

## Page Types

### Homepage (`page.tsx` at root)
- Visual-heavy: 70% design, 30% copy.
- Uses components from `src/components/fixed/` (HomeHeader, HomeBackground, etc.) and `src/components/sections/` (HomeHero, HomeFAQ, etc.).
- Custom scroll system via ScrollWrapper.
- `"use client"` is expected.

### Service Pages (`servizi/[slug]/page.tsx`)
- Copy-heavy: 30% design, 60% copy.
- Use components from `src/components/sections/` (Service* prefixed).
- i18n namespace: `Services.<slug>` (e.g., `Services.operating-partner`).
- Prefer server components. Only use `"use client"` for interactive elements (accordion, video player).
- No framer-motion; CSS animations only.

### Case Study Pages (`case-study/[slug]/page.tsx`)
- Single template, variable content from i18n JSON.
- i18n namespace: `CaseStudy.<slug>`.
- Same rules as service pages for client/server split.

## Required for Every Page

1. `generateMetadata()` with full SEO (title, description, canonical, alternates, og, twitter).
2. StructuredData component.
3. All copy from i18n JSON (never hardcoded).
4. Mobile responsive.

## Naming Convention

- Homepage components: `Home*` prefix (HomeHero, HomeFAQ, HomeFooter, HomeHeader, HomeBackground).
- Service/landing components: `Service*` prefix (ServiceHero, ServiceFAQ, ServiceFooter, ServiceHeader, ServiceBackgroundGrid).
- Shared components: no prefix, live in `src/components/shared/`.
